Mulberry Change History (MacOS)v2.0.8 : 15-Mar-2001Fixes•Fixed bug with incorrect multi-user login user id being transferred to the email address when certain admin options are configured..v2.0.7 : 9-Mar-2001Minor Changes•Added GSSAPI plugin for Kerberos 5 authentication.Fixes•Fixed bug with draft address parsing when parenthesis are in the phrase.•Fixed bug with forward quotation adding an unwanted space when no quote character is set.•Fixed bug with case-sensitive smart address testing of the default identity.•Fixed bug with Open Addressbook command/button activation.•Fixed bug with wildcard cabinet items in the copy to cabinet causing menu lock-up in disconnected mode.•Fixed bug with SMTP queue window attempting to open when its locked out.•Fixed bug with failure to find root certificates when using SSL.•Fixed bug causing a crash when parsing empty tags in styled text.•Fixed bug with dealing with disconnected playback when certain operations are missing from the playback log.•Fixed bug with parsing URLs that use the new IPv6 URL scheme for specifying a server address.v2.0.6 : 19-Jan-2001Admin Changes•Added Generate Sender admin option to force generation of Sender address if different than From.Fixes•Fixed bug causing server connect failures when changing TLS preferences without changing the server address.•Fixed bug with timezone offsets greater than 12 hrs being set to zero.•Fixed bug causing a crash in the identity edit dialog when a certain combination of admin options is set.v2.0.5 : 26-Oct-2000Fixes•Fixed bug with parts auto-expand not focussing back on the text area.•Fixed bug with use of incorrect POP3 command to initiate TLS.•Fixed bug causing a crash when attempting password changing with poppassd.•Fixed bug with mailbox window updating when quit cancelled after a mailbox is closed.•Fixed bug with parsing whitespace inside of bracketed URLs.•Fixed bug with dragging addresses around inside the group list.•Fixed bugs with PGP interoperability with format=flowed messages.•Fixed bug with incorrectly disabled SSL option for IMSP/ACAP.•Fixed bug with ACAP address books with specific types of ACAP servers.v2.0.5b3 : 04-Oct-2000Minor Changes•SSL certificate accept dialog - cancel is now the default button.•User ID & passwords fields enlarged to allow for user ids that include domain information.•A new warning alert appears when attempting to disconnect without any mail accounts set for disconnected operations.•Now preference (on by default) to do auto-expansion/collapse of message parts list when suitable attachments are present.•Added new option for PGP verify success alert.Fixes•Fixed bug with SSL padlock not appearing in mailbox window for mail accounts that can be disconnected.•Fixed bug with acceptance of SSL certs. Now requires acceptance of a cert even if the cert is the same as one previously accepted for a different server.•Fixed bug with correctly determining the server address embedded in a cert’s subject CN.v2.0.5b1/2 : 19-Sep-2000Major Changes•Added support for SSL/TLS encryption of network connections (PowerPC only).Minor Changes•Identity edit dialog controls are now enabled/disabled based on the state of the corresponding ‘Active’ checkbox.•UU-decoded attachments now use the file type/creator that best matches any file extension inthe file name.Fixes•Fixed bug in causing a crash when default identity From address was not active.•Fixed bug with quote colours not being saved when changed.•Fixed bug causing failure to remember flat/hierarchic state of local/POP3 display hierarchies.•Fixed bug with failure to decode multiple embedded UU-encoded attachments.•Fixed bug causing errors with IMAP servers returning zero-length literals.•Fixed bug with line end format when generating UU encoded attachments.v2.0.4 : 18-Aug-2000Fixes•Fixed bug in admin code when remote server is used and email address is locked.v2.0.3 : 14-Jul-2000Fixes•Fixed bug with error during specific IMSP address stores.•Fixed bug with unneeded SEARCH when opening a mailbox that would cause problems with IMAP2bis servers.•Fixed text of server parse error alert.v2.0.2 : 10-Jul-2000Minor Changes•‘Addresses to count as mine’ now accepts ‘*’ as a match to zero or more arbitrary characters at that position.Fixes•Fixed bug with inactive New button in address book manager window when local address books are locked out.•Fixed bug with moving read mail out of INBOX and selecting by flag.•Fixed bug where new address books that failed to be created were still marked for nick-name resolution etc.•Fixed bug with addressbook lookup in ACAP.•Fixed bug with group duplication after editing in a local address book.•Fixed bug causing a crash when server sends some specific broken protocol.•Fixed bug with missing default copy to with single accounts.•Fixed bug in which default dialog button was not triggering correctly in the spell check dialog.•Fixed bug with ACAP authentication.•Fixed bug with disconnect playback that could result inthe wrong mailbox being selected under particular circumstances.•Fixed bug with strict SMTP servers refusing to accept connections when the local machine’s host name cannot be determined.•Fixed bug with Reset to Default command with open message or draft windows.•Fixed bug with multiple format=flowed parameters when sending a message previously saved as a draft to a mailbox.v2.0.1 : 19-Jun-2000Minor Changes•option-click on a mailbox row will auto-match to the properties of the currently selected rows based on the column category that’s clicked on. This is currently limited to address, subject, thread and date columns.•Content-Disposition is now displayed in message parts property dialogs.•Now adds all default copy-to mailboxes in any identities to the copy to menu when it hits the ‘Too many mailboxes’ limit.•Now re-opens mailboxes that were open before a connect or disconnect operation. Window stacking order is not remembered.•Password dialog now shows the authentication mechanism that will be used.•Added new mailbox cache preference to control when the ‘Full Sort’ alert is triggered - defaults to 100 messages.•Added radio buttons to new address dialog to specify creation of ‘personal’ or ‘global’ remote address book. The ‘personal’ choice automatically adds the user id prefix to the name entered, and is the default.•Added transparent support for the non-standard AUTH=LOGIN authentication mechanism.•Now prevents users from accidently writing someone else’s preferences back over their own when quitting - mostly relevant when using Kererbos authentication where tickets can timeout.Fixes•Fixed bug with missing MIME-Version header in local messages.•Fixed bug causing a crash when registering a plugin.•Fixed missing Config plugin support.•Fixed bug with LDIF/Communicator Adbk import and line-end formats.•Fixed bug causing corrupt cached message indices when copying a message from a POP3 INBOX twice.•Fixed bug with shift-up-arrow not scrolling a table.•Fixed bug with remote prefs upgrade from v1.x not writing back all upgraded prefs.•Fixed bug with UU-decoding detecting the wrong start to uu data.•Fixed bug with message window styles being lost on text after printing.•Fixed bug with mailbox listing for disconected support when using a UW-style server.•Fixed bug with copy-to mailboxes failing to work when they only appear in the Subscribed list and not in any display hierarchy.•Fixed bug with certain characters in dictionary path causing dictionaries not to be found.•Fixed bug causing a crash when renaming the path to a local mailbox/adbk that Mulberry is using.•Fixed bug with disconnected partial messages missing the MIME-Version header.•Fixed bug with failure to properly recognise multiple SMTP AUTH and AUTH= responses.•Fixed bugs in DIGEST-MD5 plugin.v2.0 : 30-Mar-2000Minor Changes•Auto-creation of default IMSP address book now sets address book options.Fixes•Fixed bugs when running from a locked disk.•Fixed bug causing a crash when quitting with an open single server window.•Fixed bug causing a crash when dragging items out of the group edit dialog and exiting with OK.•Fixed bug where new mailboxes added to a brand new local account could have a messed up hierarchy display.•Fixed bug where address book disconnected operation menu commands were not active for an address book window.•Fixed bug with messed up mailbox hierarchy display when the first subscribed mailbox is not at the top of its hierarchy.•Fixed bug with duplicate addresses appearing after message drag and drop onto address book manager item.•Fixed bug with conversion of v1.4 alert sound preference.•Fixed bug with Save User ID preference being off when using Admin Tool configuration causing multiple password dialogs to appear.•Fixed bugs related to timezone and daylight savings changes and how they interact with the file system file modtimes.v2.0b12 : 16-Mar-2000Minor Changes•LDAP searches now recognise multiple values for certain attribute types.•Added ‘None’ button to the mailbox browse dialog when saving a copy of sent mail.•AppleDouble parts in flat mode now display the type/subtype of the data sub-part of the multipart.•Added ‘New Address Book’ dialog for creating a new address book and setting the various address book options. Defaults to nick-names and searches on.Fixes•Fixed quoted printable decode bug with non-text attachments.•Fixed bug with clickable empty URLs.•Fixed bug with use of temporary draft files when booted from a CD.•Fixed bug causing a crash when attempting to verify a malformed multipart/signed message.•Fixed bug with local address books using only the full name as the record key.•Fixed bug in which the connect/disconnect state would not be remembered in the local prefs file if using a remote prefs set on startup.•Fixed bug with copy to mailboxes not being renamed when an account is renamed, for identities other than the default.•Fixed bug with failure to properly select the first new message when opening a mailbox sorted by something other than message number.•Fixed bug with menu id clashes with third-party extensions.•Fixed bug which allowed a user to attempt to download a non-cached disconnected attachment.•Fixed bug causing a crash when SMTP queue window fails to open.•Fixed bug with incorrect page setup being used when printing from a mailbox window.•Fixed bug with saving disconnected preferences when the preference file has to be created the first time.•Fixed bug with Date Received mailbox window information being off by one month for any local mailbox. Mailbox caches have to be reset manually.•Fixed bug with setting the copy to mailbox in the Simple preferences panel when Copy To None is set in the default identity.•Fixed bug causing display update problems when deleting an address book.v2.0b11 : 22-Feb-2000Fixes•Fixed bug with 19782 errors with long server lines.•Fixed bug with vers resource count.v2.0b10 : 21-Feb-2000Minor Changes•Legitimate server errors during playback now result in any pending EXPUNGE’s being removed from the playback queue.•When a connection is rejected, the IP address cache for that server is now reset.Fixes•Fixed bug in LDAP full name results.•Fixed bug with failure to quit when writing IMSP prefs fails.•Fixed bug with drag and drop between different text areas in the same window.•Fixed bug with failure to delete local folders whenb corresponding mailbox is deleted.•Fixed bug with text between <STYLE> tags in HTML appearing in messages.•Fixed bug causing a crash when local address books are locked out by admin tool.•Fixed bug with Mac->ISO-8859-1 conversion.•Fixed bug with playback action being deleted when failure occurs but its not been completed.•Fixed bug with NULL characters in message body resulting in truncated text display.•Fixed bug with alert styles other than the having items locked when Internet Config is used.•Fixed bug with cabinet items whose account name contains a directory separator character.•Fixed bug with playback flag action compacting.•Fixed bug with ‘leaked’ connections when viewing message search results.•Fixed bug in parsing capability response.v2.0b9 : 9-Feb-2000Minor Changes•Switched Details and Options buttons in Mailbox properties dialog so that Options is the first one shown.Fixes•Fixed parsing of LDAP mail attribute to work with RFC822-style address with comments.•Fixed rare bug in IMAP error recovery code that could cause a crash if server returned illegal IMAP protocol.•Fixed bug with Mailbox Create command acting on a Cabinet.•Fixed bug with Search criteria popups not being initialised when switching between some criteria types.•Fixed bug in which alerts could not be dismissed.•Fixed bug causing a crash when switching from a set of preferences with a remote prefs account to one without.•Fixed bug causing process deadlock when doing Update then Disconnect with drafts in the SMTP queue and certain port-forwarding software is in use.•Fixed bug with some Navigation Services alerts appearing on top of the Status window.•Automatic local address books with arbitrary line-ends can now be read correctly.•Fixed bug with quoted-printable decoding of non-text parts.•Fixed bug with use of an incorrect memory allocator that could cause low memory errors with large cached mailboxes.•Fixed bug causing a crash when sending a draft with no parts.•Fixed bugs with print captions when a requested address field is empty.v2.0b8 : 26-Jan-2000Minor Changes•Changed format of X-Mailer header to be similar to News’ User-Agent header and removed display of serial number.•Message window parts list automatically expands if there are no displayable parts and suitable text is displayed in the message body area.•Content-Type column header in message parts list now includes flat/hierarchic indicator.•Copy Now command is active for a selection in the mailbox window and results in a mailbox Choose dialog for copying.•Address expansion dialog now supports multiple selections.Fixes•Fixed bug in format=flowed display support for quoted text.•Fixed processing of subject & body items in extended mailto URL handling.•Fixed bug with wrapping of long subjects in the header.•Fixed minor balloon help issues in prefs dialog.•Fixed bug causing a crash when attempting to drag a cabinet in the server window.•Fixed bug with line-end conversion in non-text parts that Mulberry displays as text.•Fixed bug with locked entry fields in Simple prefs panel when Internet Config is in use.•Fixed bug causing a crash when server disconnects during playback.v2.0b7 : 03-Jan-2000Minor Changes•SMTP queue window now uses a different icon for messages that failed to be sent.•New option to have draft messages opened from a mailbox deleted when the draft is sent or saved again.•Can optionally prevent deletion of drafts if they have the important flag set.Fixes•Fixed bug causing a crash when SMTP send fails.•Fixed bug with failure to alert user of held messages in the SMTP queue when quitting or disconnecting.•Fixed bug with URL activation when URL is at the very end of a message with no line break after it.•Fixed bug causing a crash when quoted-printable encoding is used on a binary file.•Fixed bug causing a crash when base64 encoding is used with the wrap length set to less than 76 characters.v2.0b6 : 24-Dec-1999Minor Changes•SMTP queue window title now also displays the name of the queue and its enabled status.•Added command key equivalent for Open Mailboxes command.Fixes•Fixed bug with failure to read spelling preferences.•Fixed bug with unitialised SMTP hold preference.•Fixed bug with spaces at the end of hrad-wrapped lines when generating format=flowed.•Fixed bug with usenet style signatures when viewing format=flowed.•Fixed bug with stuck Speech preference dialog button.•Fixed bug with inactive copy to defaulting to choose later.•Fixed bug with formatting of string list preferences.•Fixed bug with creation of mailboxes with illegal names starting with directory separator character.•Fixed various issues related to reverse DNS lookup delays.•Fixed bug with incorrect encoding of 8-bit MIME parameters.•Fixed bug with enabled state of new mail sound popup when dialog first opened.v2.0b5 : 17-Dec-1999Minor Changes•Now alerts the user on startup when there is less than a week to go in demo mode or beta expirary.•Can now register unregistered copy from the About Box.•LDAP search now only asks for the attributes needed, unless putting them in the Notes field.•Added basic format=flowed support.•Added new preference to have tied identities triggered when the ‘New Draft’ command or ‘Draft’ button is used when appropriate.•The browse for mailboxes dialog is now resizable and remembers its size and position.•Added NTLM authentication plugin.•Added new preference for each SMTP account to allow drafts to be inserted into the SMTP queue in ‘held’ state.•Can now copy sub-messages (digest contents) to any mailbox.•Now generates an alert on startup or restart if any form of protocol logging is turned on, and allows it to be turned off.•Added new Admin option to turn off protocol logging.•Now remembers the last preference panel selected.Fixes•Fixed bug with redraw of authentication panels.•Fixed bug which allowed a draft file to be opened more than once.•Fixed bug with MIME encoded 8-bit headers that contained a comma.•Fixed bug with failure to generate new mail alerts for open mailboxes.•Fixed bug causing a crash on exit when running on 68K machines with OpenTransport.•Fixed bug in which attached text files would be hard-wrapped when sent.•Fixed bug in which expunge on close was not done when switching to the next new mailbox.•Fixed bug that could cause a crash after changing preferences and then using a local address book.•Fixed bug with long initial connect times when used on a machine on a LAN using NAT.•Fixed bug in which editing an identity would lose tied identity links to mailboxes.v2.0b4 : 1-Dec-1999Fixes•Fixed bug with anonymous authentication failure.v2.0b3 : 30-Nov-1999Fixes•Fixed bug with incorrect text display of a message containing no displayable parts.v2.0b2 : 29-Nov-1999Minor Changes•Moved tab and wrapping checkboxes in Outgoing prefs panel.•Group edit dialog enlarged.•Can now have Copy To popup default to ‘Choose Later’ by turning on copying, but leaving the mailbox name empty.•Authentication plugins are now dynamic.•New DIGEST-MD5 authentication plugin.•Single selection in the New Messages cabinet is now moved to the next mailbox in that cabinet if the selected mailbox is removed.•Edit and delete of display hierarchies can now only be done via menu commands.Fixes•Fixed bug with <AREA> tag in HTML.•Fixed bug with unresponsive OK button in diconnected dialog.•Fixed state of ‘Also Quote whole Message’ checkbox in prefs.•Fixed mailbox advanced prefs radio groups.•Fixed bug when trying to cancel a disconnect operation.•Fixed bug with open/close state of SMTP queue window not being remembered.•Fixed bug in which addresses used in drag and drop were not filtered for ‘smart’ addresses.•Fixed bug causing a crash when network connection dies during Properties on a network address book.•Fixed bug with count of parts when parts table is flat.•Fixed bug with Internet Config overwriting some Admin Locks.•Fixed bug that made new POP3 INBOX’s open when Mulberry started or prefs reset.•Fixed various help balloons in prefs dialog.•Fixed bug with MIME parts not saving properly when the name had a ‘:’ in it.•Fixed bug with partial FETCH’ing resulting in the first character of some disconnected messages being lost.•Fixed bugs with converting line-ends in c-style escaped address fields.•Fixed bug with failure of PGP to warn when an encryption key was missing.•Fixed bugs with mailbox window updating when sorting by flag.•Fixed bug with address expansion occurring when closing a draft window.•Fixed ‘display’ hierarchy terminology in various places.v2.0b1 : 21-Oct-1999Minor Changes•Can now edit bounced message subject.•Security tabs are now hidden if no suitable plugin is available.Fixes•Fixed bug where message window parts hierarchic state was not remembered between launches.•Fixed bug where adding a new text part to a bounce would select the wrong part.•Fixed bug with zero width columns being read from preferences.•Fixed bug when starting up without any preferences and attempting to use IMSP.v2.0a8 : 15-Oct-1999Minor Changes•Added ‘quick selection’ buttons to reply addressing dialog.•Added new Draft menu items for signing/encrypting and DSN notifications.•Added new warning dialog when using the delete mailbox command on a cabinet item.•Can now change a MIME parts disposition on outgoing mail.•Can now append drafts to a mailbox from which parts of the draft were obtained.•Spelling dictionary is now stored using a relative path if its in the Mulberry directory.•Added options to POP3 accounts to allow skipping of messages over a certain size.•Changed Simple prefs panel to allow a choice of IMAP, POP3 or Local mail account.Fixes•Fixed bugs with failure to quote when forwarding without a selection.•Fixed bugs relating to changes in the mailbox list when disconnected.•Fixed bug with incorrect error message when an authentication fails due to a missing plugin.•Fixed bug with incompatibilites between v1.4 and v2.0a preferences.•Fixed bug with incorrect disconnect status on startup.v2.0a7 : 8-Oct-1999Minor Changes•Identities can now be re-ordered via drag and drop in the preferences dialog.•Added a new preference option to have the first message/rfc822 in a multipart/digest open automatically when the its message is opened.•Added ‘Entire Message’ searchg criteria to allow searching of both the header and body.•When forwarding a message from a message window, the quotation is now determined by any selection in the message window (can include headers if shown).Fixes•Fixed bugs with local mailboxes using non-native line-end conventions.•Fixed issues with two local items in addressbook manager window.•Fixed bug with illegal FETCH items during playback.•Fixed bug with failure to warn on UIDValidity mismatch.•Fixed bug with improper case-sensitive comparisons of content-types.•Fixed bug with focus change due to identity popup change.•Fixed bug with empty draft window title when subject is deleted.•Fixed bug with disconnect dialog twist button state getting out of sync.•Fixed bug with mailbox browse dialog with a single server and display hierarchy.v2.0a6 : 30-Sep-1999Minor Changes•Added some address expansion options.•Added URL Seen colour and style to prefs.•Disconnect dialog now allows a choice of which mailboxes to synchronise when disconnecting.•Disconnect dialog now shows some level of ‘progress’ while connecting or disconnecting.•Added option to turn off SMTP queuing for each SMTP account.•Default location for local files can now be switched between the application folder and the OS’s default ‘user documents’ folder.•Local mailbox accounts can now use a line-end convention different from the OS’s standard as set in the prefs.•Send button in draft window is disabled if current SMTP account does not queue and Mulberry is disconnected.•SMTP queue window is disabled if there are no SMTP accounts enabled for queueing.•When saving a draft to the IMAP server as a draft, ‘unspecified-recipients’ is no longer added to the To field when there are no addresses specified.Fixes•Fixed bug in disconnect playback with UID values not being sorted.•Fixed bug when attempting to save a draft with a subject that contains illegal characters in the OS’s filesystem.•Fixed bug in which deleting a mailbox would also remove any wildcard cabinet items that matched it.•Fixed a bug in which renamed cabinet items were not actually renamed in the preferences.•Fixed a bug in which cursor spinning would affect the state of the cursor in other foreground applications.•Fixed bugs with toggling relative/absolute path radio buttons in local prefs panels.•Fixed bugs in local RFC822 parser MIME parameter values ‘folded’ across lines.•Fixed bug with failure to honor Content-Disposition filename parameter.•Fixed bugs with multiple alert style checking not being done on some styles.•Fixed bug with empty lines in identity X-Headers.•Fixed bug with reply/forward quoting text with lines that start with spaces or tabs that exceed the wrap length.•Fixed bug with handling illegal ‘&’ characters in HTML.•Fixed bug with tab selection of next new mailbox in server window.•Fixed bug with cross-platform password encryption/decryption.v2.0a5 : 27-Aug-1999Minor Changes•Added context menu Expand Address command for address fields.•Changed SMTP queue related menu commands in File menu.•Now get an alert when connected and sending a message when the SMTP queue is disabled.•SMTP Queue window now pops up when connecting without enabling the queue when messages are present in the queue.•The full format of date is displayed in the message window date sent field.Fixes•Fixed bug with position flat/hierarchic parts toggle button on message window resize.•Fixed bug in which double-click of text list dialog did not do OK action.•Fixed bug in which favourite button in server window column would not work for cabinet items.•Fixed bug with Nav Services preview being disabled.•Fixed bug in generating folded MIME-encoded non-ascii headers.•Fixed bug with non-OS specific spell check dictionary location preference.•Fixed bug causing a crash when disconnecting and synchronising a deep mailbox list.•Fixed bug with address expansion and addresses on multiple lines.•Fixed bugs in disconnected playback when UIDValidity mismatch or other errors occur.•Fixed bug with log files failing to be flushed after every entry.•Fixed bug with shift-arrow key selection in edit fields.v2.0a4 : 23-Aug-1999Minor Changes•SMTP Queue window is opened on startup if connection is in place but queues are disabled.•POP3 connect option to do update then disconnect check.•Mailbox list can now be fully synchronised on disconnect.•Added button to server window size column to allow calculation of mailbox size when its not been previously done.•Originator-Info header is no longer sent by default. Admins have to explicitly turn this on if required.•New draft title and file name is now based on the subject of the draft.•Message windows can now be reused with option-double-click opening a message. Behaviour can be toggled with a new preference.•Search Hierarchy has been renamed to Display Hierarchy and menus/UI reorganised.•Added new menu commands for manipulating cabinets.•Local/POP3 accounts now display their mailboxes as a flat list when only one search hierarchy is present.•Message window parts list can now be displayed flat (the new default) or fully hierarchic as controlled by a new button. The state is saved in prefs.•Multiple alert styles which can be applied to any cabinet now available via prefs.•Removed ‘goto’ button in mailbox window and replaced with two new menu commands.•Added ‘Expand Address’ command to do address expansion in a draft window address field.•IMSP address book opening time reduced.Fixes•Fixed bug in POP3 implementation when server does not support UIDL.•Fixed bug when server window size column was displayed during connect/disconnect.•Fixed bug with defaulting of content-type of a multipart/digest in local RFC822 parser.•Fixed bug with local RFC822 parsing of certain multipart boundary sequences.•Fixed bug with adding a mailbox to a cabinet with only a folder in it.•Fixed bug with logout failing to refresh server window row.•Fixed bug causing a crash when quitting with an active SMTP queue.•Fixed bug with AppleDouble part size calculation for admin limits.•Fixed bug with inability to switch to connected mode when using a modem that is already dialed-in.•Fixed bugs in dot-stuffing attachments from an IMAP server being sent directly over SMTP.•Fixed bug with byte-ordering of password encoding in cross-platform prefs files.•Fixed bugs with runs of MIME-encoded non-ascii headers.•Fixed bug with server window updating when connecting/disconnecting.•Fixed bugs with cache/index file mod-times and timezone/daylight savings changes.•Fixed bugs with spell checker refusing to delete or add certain words.•Fixed bug in base64 decoding of ISO-8859-1 text.•Fixed bug in which keystrokes from the mailbox browse dialog were leaking into windows behind it.•Fixed bug in which a new local was not being created with a default search hierarchy.•Fixed bugs related to address search window state saving and loading from prefs.•Fixed bugs with enabling/disabling copy controls in the message window.•Fixed bug when mailbox was set to expunge on close and mark seen on close.•Fixed bug with re-use of connections during playback.v2.0a3 : 9-Jul-1999Minor Changes•ACL panel now includes mailbox popup and ‘Apply to All’ to enable batch ACL setting.•Added ‘Recipient’ and ‘Correspondent’ search criteria items.Fixes•Fixed bug in base64 decoding.•Fixed bug with incorrect UID FETCH during disconnect.•Fixed bugs with POP3 INBOX index/cache corruption.•Fixed bugs related to POP3 UIDL recognition.•Fixed bug that resulted in an APPEND being used instead of a COPY when doing a playback.•Fixed bugs in nested multipart RFC822 parsing.•Fixed bugs with thread deadlock when using ‘Update then Disconnect’ with queued messages.v2.0a2 : 16-Jun-1999Major Changes•Mulberry now supports disconnected preferences.•Mulberry now supports disconnected address books with basic synchronisation.Minor Changes•Added commands to Windows menu to facilitate expanding and collapsing of various window areas.•Added preference to allow APOP authentication to be disabled.•New ‘automatica’ local address book storage.•‘Automatic’ local address books can now be used when closed.•No longer requires UIDPLUS support for disconnected use.•Added SMTP Queue window for manipulating SMTP queues.•Added Print command to text area context menus.•Disconnect/conect options now saved in preferences.•Logging dialog allows disconnected playback operations to be logged.•Can now type characters in server window to select items in the list.Fixes•Fixed MIME header decoding in local messages.•Fixed bug causing hang when doing Properties on a local/disconnected mailbox.•Fixed bug causing a POP3 network connection when disconnected.•Fixed bug with ‘Copy INBOX Messages being Replied to’.•Fixed bugs with naming of local disconnected mailboxes.•Fixed disconnect menu wording and state.•Fixed bugs when unseen messages are treated as ‘new’.•Fixed bugs with hierarchic New Messages cabinet.•Fixed bugs when deleting a mailbox with a sub-hierarchy.•Fixed bug to prevent adding non-disconnectable mailboxes to auto-sync cabinet.•Fixed bug with cursor positioning in newly created draft windows.•Fixed local searching so that threads yield to each other.•Fixed bugs when closing/quitting while searching.•Fixed problems with Reply-To address and local messages.•Fixed bug with seen flag being set on popped messages.v2.0a1 : 23-Apr-1999Major Changes-General•Mulberry now supports local and POP3 mail accounts.•IMAP accounts can work in disconnected mode - using fully synchronising playback.•New ‘Disconnected Mode...’ menu command to switch between disconnected and online.•Disconnection can control modem dial/hangup.•Full set of user options available for controlling disconnecting and re-connecting.•SMTP sending now operates in the background.•SMTP queue can be manually paused, and also honors disconnected state.•Added DIGEST-MD5 authentication capability (plugin not shipping as yet).•Added PGP inline and OpenPGP support (plugin not shipping as yet).-Preferences•Preferences merged for all OS’es.•Single IMSP default options set for all OS’es.•Multiple window states now saved in a single prefs set for each screen size and OS used.•Added ‘Security’ panel for controlling security plugins (e.g. PGP).•Added new Mailbox ‘Disconnected’ panel.-Identities•Can now inherit from any identity - not just the default identity.•Added new ‘Outgoing’ section.•Can specifiy default To, CC and Bcc addresses in Outgoing section which get added to drafts using that identity.•Added support for requesting DSN’s in Outgoing section.•Added ‘Security’ section for controlling signing and encryption of messages sent with that identity.•Added ‘Also Copy Original Message’ to Options section to have the corresponding checkbox in a draft window automatically set when that identity is chosen.-Server Window•New ‘Auto Synchronise’ cabinet for specifiying which mailboxes are to be synchronised on disconnect.•Added ‘Size’ column for display of mailbox size.•Mailbox properties dialog: added controls to support new options.•New icons to represent servers for different account types.•New icons for local and disconnected mailboxes.-Mailbox Window•New state icon to show online, local and disconnected mailbox state.•Added ‘Disconnected’ column to indicate state of messages in disconnected cache.-Message Window•Added new control to collpase/expand header area.•Added new icon used in parts table to indicate a message part in a disconnected mailbox that has not yet been locally cached.-Draft Window•Added new control to collapse/expand header area.•Added sign and encrypt buttons (only displayed when security plugin installed).